  <h2>Surgical Care You Can Trust</h2>
  <p>
    When your pet needs surgery, you want to know they're in capable, caring hands. At Healthy Paws Animal Hospital, Dr. Burgess and our surgical team approach every procedure with meticulous preparation, advanced monitoring, and a genuine commitment to your pet's comfort and safety. We understand that surgery can be stressful for you as a pet owner, and we take the time to explain every step of the process so you feel confident in your pet's care.
  </p>

  <h2>Our Surgical Services</h2>
  <p>
    Our modern surgery suite is equipped to handle a wide range of procedures, including:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Soft tissue surgery</strong> — mass removals, bladder stone surgery, wound repair, abdominal exploratory procedures, and more</li>
    <li><strong><a href="/spay-neuter-lake-in-the-hills-il/">Spay and neuter</a></strong> — routine reproductive surgeries performed with individualized pain management</li>
    <li><strong>Dental surgery</strong> — complex extractions and oral procedures (see our <a href="/dental-care/">dental care</a> page for more details)</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency surgery</strong> — urgent procedures for acute conditions like foreign body ingestion, lacerations, and other time-sensitive situations</li>
    <li><strong>Orthopedic referrals</strong> — for procedures like ACL repair that require specialized surgical expertise, we work with trusted board-certified surgeons and coordinate your pet's care from start to finish</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What Sets Our Surgical Care Apart</h2>

  <h3>Pre-Surgical Bloodwork</h3>
  <p>
    Before any procedure involving anesthesia, we recommend <a href="/laboratory-diagnostics/">pre-surgical bloodwork</a> to evaluate your pet's organ function. These tests help us identify any underlying conditions that could affect how your pet processes anesthesia, allowing us to tailor the anesthetic protocol to your pet's specific needs.
  </p>

  <h3>Dedicated Anesthesia Monitoring</h3>
  <p>
    Safety during surgery starts with careful anesthesia management. A dedicated team member monitors your pet's vital signs throughout the entire procedure, tracking:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Heart rate and rhythm (ECG)</li>
    <li>Blood pressure</li>
    <li>Blood oxygen saturation (pulse oximetry)</li>
    <li>Respiratory rate and carbon dioxide levels</li>
    <li>Body temperature</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    This comprehensive monitoring allows us to make real-time adjustments and respond immediately if any parameter changes.
  </p>

  <h3>Individualized Pain Management</h3>
  <p>
    We believe no pet should experience unnecessary pain. Our team uses a <a href="/pain-management/">multimodal pain management</a> approach, combining different types of pain relief to provide the most effective comfort. Pain management begins before surgery (pre-emptive analgesia), continues during the procedure, and extends into the recovery period at home.
  </p>

  <h3>Personal Follow-Up by Dr. Burgess</h3>
  <p>
    After surgery and significant procedures, Dr. Burgess personally follows up to check on your pet's recovery. This is part of our commitment to care that goes beyond the procedure itself — we want to make sure your pet is healing well and that you have the support you need during the recovery period.
  </p>

  <h2>What to Expect on Surgery Day</h2>
  <p>
    We know surgery day can feel overwhelming. Here's what the process typically looks like:
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Morning drop-off</strong> — You'll bring your pet in at a scheduled time. Our team will answer any last-minute questions and confirm the surgical plan.</li>
    <li><strong>Pre-surgical assessment</strong> — We perform a physical exam and review bloodwork results before proceeding.</li>
    <li><strong>The procedure</strong> — Your pet receives individualized anesthesia and is monitored continuously throughout surgery.</li>
    <li><strong>Recovery</strong> — Your pet wakes up in a warm, quiet recovery area under close supervision.</li>
    <li><strong>Discharge</strong> — We'll call you when your pet is ready to go home, and our team will review detailed aftercare instructions in person.</li>
    <li><strong>Follow-up</strong> — Dr. Burgess checks in on your pet's recovery, and we schedule any needed follow-up appointments.</li>
  </ol>
